Tailor (42)
<BR>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uwhorlwinnd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whorl Winnd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b><font color=yellow>RA Council Member</font><br><font color=blue>Administrator<b></span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/4/01 8:19:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Monks, help me out here!</span><hr size=1> Just like Gaffy said, it's situational.  For me, if the night is coming to an end, and everyone will be calling it quits after the evac, heck ya, I wanna be in it too.  Otherwise, if everyone will be coming back into the dungeon, I'd much rather stay behind.  Mainly to drag any corpses that didn't make it in the evac.  Also, as hard as it is to do..don't prematurely evac before it's called out.  Sometimes, yeah, you can obviously see the 20 things following the monk back that he can't see.  Most of the time if you have a Monk in the group, the Monk will be the one that calls out the evac because he/she will know if too many baddies were brought back, or whether the party can handle them.  <br>
<br>
  Another thing kinda off topic on the subject... Many groups form up, and decide on an "evac" caller.  This is the one person that will decide if an evac is needed.  While this sounds like a good idea, unless that person is a fairly confident person IRL, he/she may call out evac too late fearing the dreaded non-needed evac.  IMO, it's much better to make anyone in the group able to call out Evac...most people won't feel comfortable calling it out, but the ones that do will be certain that it is needed, saving everyones lives in the process.   <p><b><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=74483 target="web"><font color=blue>
Whorl Winnd</font></a><BR>
51st Season Human Disciple<BR>
Morell-Thule<BR>
[Random Acts] of Kindness!

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ugwion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gwion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b><font color=yellow>RA Council Member</font><br><b><font color=blue>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 985<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/4/01 12:29:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Monks, help me out here!</span><hr size=1> Thanks, guys.  One other thing non-porting classes have to remember is the evacer can sometimes get you right back where you were -- often, it's a matter of a simple port and a short run, and everybody lives.  (I'm thinking specifically of Crystal Caverns or The Tower of Frozen Shadow here; I admit with some places it's a lot tougher).<br>
<br>
Another thing, communication is key.  There's nothing I hate more than seeing a big &quot;NO DONT DO IT YET&quot; right before the LOADING, PLEASE WAIT comes up.  It's a lot better to work it out ahead of time.<br>
<br>
Finally, please refrain from giving the evacer a bunch of crap because you wouldn't have made the same call in the same situation.  I don't get mad at tanks when they do a bad pull; please show your transportation specialist the same courtesy. <p><font color=green face="ARIAL, HELVETICA, LUCIDA SANS"><B>Gwion Llewellyn</B></font><BR> Level, um, 39<BR>Useful druid of Tunare!<BR>
