</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/brandomacts.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thissylsouldefiler>Thissyl Souldefiler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/5/01 8:53:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evac ? what evac ? you mean you don't have FD ? oh girl.</span><hr size=1> Coming from the &quot;other&quot; class with FD, I say take the group with you and I'll buy you some time. Being particularly heroic is not quite a necormantic trait, but it's one I exhibit on occasion.<br>
<br>
I tend to want to agree with some of the other posts. It all depends on the monk. Some don't want to be the scapegoat, and want to go with the group on the evac- those are the &quot;non-group-minded&quot; monks.  The others tend to think like me, and will throw the offensive gear in so the druid or wizard can get an evac. I suggest asking the monk...most will buy you time.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I hope this helps!<br>
